Visualization: Case 2- Reduce Hospital Stay Duration to Improve Recovery Rates 6


Positive Insight:

Patients staying over 7.5 days have lower recovery rate. For example, in February, longer stays (8.16 days) reduced recovery rates by 23%. In contrast, shorter stays (6.87 days in July) boosted recovery by 7%, highlighting the potential impact of optimizing stay duration.




Negative Insight:

Longer stays increase treatment costs. In November, stays of 8.71 days increased treatment costs by 16%, while shorter stays (6.62 days in January) reduced costs by 2%. Optimizing hospital stay duration can prevent cost overruns and improve resource use.




Case 2 ROI:

Reducing hospital stay duration could save $3.7 million annually, with a 180% ROI. Efficient management will improve recovery rates and reduce treatment costs.
